quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  6,74,"And ЋєrememberЋЇ when Abraham said to his father, »Вzar, вАЬDo you take idols as gods? It is clear to me that you and your people are entirely misguided.вАЭ"
  6,75,"We also showed Abraham the wonders of the heavens and the earth, so he would be sure in faith"
  6,76,"When the night grew dark upon him, he saw a star and said, вАЬThis is my Lord!вАЭ But when it set, he said, вАЬI do not love things that set.вАЭ"
  6,77,"Then when he saw the moon rising, he said, вАЬThis one is my Lord!вАЭ But when it disappeared, he said, вАЬIf my Lord does not guide me, I will certainly be one of the misguided people.вАЭ"
  6,78,"Then when he saw the sun shining, he said, вАЬThis must be my LordвАФit is the greatest!вАЭ But again when it set, he declared, вАЬO my people! I totally reject whatever you associate Ћєwith God in worshipЋЇ"
  6,79,I have turned my face towards the One Who has originated the heavens and the earthвАФbeing uprightвАФand I am not one of the polytheists.вАЭ
  6,80,"And his people argued with him. He responded, вАЬAre you arguing with me about God, while He has guided me? I am not afraid of whatever ЋєidolsЋЇ you associate with HimвАФЋєnone can harm me,ЋЇ unless my Lord so wills. My Lord encompasses everything in ЋєHisЋЇ knowledge. Will you not be mindful"
  6,81,"And how should I fear your associate-gods, while you have no fear in associating ЋєothersЋЇ with GodвАФa practice He has never authorized? Which side has more right to security? ЋєTell meЋЇ if you really know!вАЭ"
  6,82,It is ЋєonlyЋЇ those who are faithful and do not tarnish their faith with falsehood¬†who are guaranteed security and are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided
  6,83,"This was the argument We gave Abraham against his people. We elevate in rank whoever We please. Surely your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,84,"And We blessed him with Isaac and Jacob. We guided them all as We previously guided Noah and those among his descendants: David, Solomon, Job, Joseph, Moses, and Aaron. This is how We reward the good-doers"
  6,85,"Likewise, ЋєWe guidedЋЇ Zachariah, John, Jesus, and Elias, who were all of the righteous"
  6,86,"ЋєWe also guidedЋЇ Ishmael, Elisha, Jonah, and Lot, favouring each over other people Ћєof their timeЋЇ"
  6,87,"And ЋєWe favouredЋЇ some of their forefathers, their descendants, and their brothers. We chose them and guided them to the Straight Path"
  6,88,"This is GodвАЩs guidance with which He guides whoever He wills of His servants. Had they associated others with Him Ћєin worshipЋЇ, their ЋєgoodЋЇ deeds would have been wasted"
  6,89,"Those were the ones to whom We gave the Scripture, wisdom, and prophethood. But if these ЋєpagansЋЇ disbelieve in this ЋєmessageЋЇ, then We have already entrusted it to a people who will never disbelieve in it"
  6,90,"These ЋєprophetsЋЇ were ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided by God, so follow their guidance. Say, вАЬI ask no reward of you for this ЋєQuranЋЇвАФit is a reminder to the whole world.вАЭ"
  6,91,"And they¬†have not shown God His proper reverence when they said, вАЬGod has revealed nothing to any human being.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬWho then revealed the Book brought forth by Moses as a light and guidance for people, which you split into separate sheetsвАФrevealing some and hiding much? You have been taught Ћєthrough this QuranЋЇ what neither you nor your forefathers knew.вАЭ Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬGod Ћєrevealed itЋЇ!вАЭ Then leave them to amuse themselves with falsehood"
  6,92,This is a blessed Book which We have revealedвАФconfirming what came before itвАФso you may warn the Mother of Cities¬†and everyone around it. Those who believe in the Hereafter ЋєtrulyЋЇ believe in it and guard their prayers
  6,93,"Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies against God or claims, вАЬI have received revelations!вАЭвАФalthough nothing was revealed to themвАФor the one who says, вАЬI can reveal the like of GodвАЩs revelations!вАЭ? If you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ could only see the wrongdoers in the throes of death while the angels are stretching out their hands ЋєsayingЋЇ, вАЬGive up your souls! Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for telling lies about God and for being arrogant towards His revelations!вАЭ"
  6,94,ЋєTodayЋЇ you have come back to Us all alone as We created you the first timeвАФleaving behind everything We have provided you with. We do not see your intercessors with youвАФthose you claimed were GodвАЩs partners Ћєin worshipЋЇ. All your ties have been broken and all your claims have let you down.вАЭ